<br>
However, if your talking about guilds that operates with a purpose and charter and do the occasional roleplaying event or even roleplay within guildchat, then there are a few guilds still out there.  Although they are few and far between as far as I can see.<br>
<br>
Sad to say guilds like Shield of Kaladim and Vale Patrol are long gone.  (At least I assume they're gone.  I havent seen any of them for awhile now.  Forgive me if there are still active)  Those guilds had a specific recruitment policy and stuck to it for roleplay reasons.  I believe The Sisterhood was one of the last of these types of guilds, and even they no longer exist as such.<br>
<br>
Still, there are guilds out there that do roleplay in limited ways.  The Watchmen, for example, expects its members to roleplay to a certain extant.  While we dont roleplay all the time, its rare a day will go by that you wont see something going on in guildchat, and I dont mean people speaking Ogre.<br>
<br>
One thing to do in looking for guilds that do limited roleplaying is to check their website.  One key thing is to check their officer titles.  You can generally ignore guilds with officer titles like Grand Dragon or Lord High Bugglebop.  The guilds that do roleplaying have a public history that fits within the EQ world and their officer titles reflect that.  Often they have histories for each member that is roleplayed.  Finally they will probably have some sort of stories section in their message board.<br>
<br>
The guilds that totally roleplay are, for the most part, long gone.  And I doubt you'll ever find them to any extent in any online game.  But the guilds that support and encourage limited roleplaying are alive and well, both on Karana and other servers.<br>
<br>
I wouldnt look for a guild that really roleplays.  Check with your friends and see which guilds they're in.  Then check those guilds out.  I wouldnt expect that most of them roleplay to any great extent, but if you and a few others are willing to, its amazing what you can start up.  <br>
<br>
Roleplaying isnt something happens around you.  Roleplaying is something that you actively create and take a part in.  Its hard to find a play when your a member of the audience.  You need to be in a specific place after all.  But if your an actor you can put on a performance no matter where you are.<br>
